The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Fast bowlers camp begins today
Bangalore: Yoga sessions and Kapil Devs tips will be the highlights at the five-day camp for Indias leading fast bowlers beginning on Tuesday. Sixteen bowlers will attend the camp where fitness will be the focus of attention. Zaheer Khan is the man missing and will join the combined fitness camp that commences on June 13. There is one bowler from Bengal in the bunch  Shib Shankar Paul  who had a rich haul of wickets in the Ranji Trophy and Duleep Trophy. The BCCI secretary S.K. Nair informed that Kapil will be at the camp from Friday to June 16. Team India physical trainer Gregory Allen King will put the bowlers through their paces. King appeared satisfied with the progress made by the pacemen in terms of fitness since the last camp in August and added there is room to improve. Yoga instructor S.N. Omkar, who was involved with the last camp too, said attention will be paid to injury prevention and warming-up. (PTI)  Copyright 
